\n\\n# Create artifact directory\\nif [ -z \\\"${E2E_ARTIFACT_DIR:-}\\\" ]; then\\n  E2E_ARTIFACT_DIR=\\\"$PWD/e2e/artifacts/$(date +%Y-%m-%dT%H-%M-%S)\\\"\\nfi\\nexport E2E_ARTIFACT_DIR\\nmkdir -p \\\"$E2E_ARTIFACT_DIR\\\"\\n\\n# Run tests with gotestsum and generate report\\ngotestsum --format dots --jsonfile \\\"$E2E_ARTIFACT_DIR/test-events.json\\\" -- \\\\\\n  -tags=e2e -count=1 -timeout=30m \\\\\\n  ${filter:+-run \\\"$filter\\\"} \\\\\\n  ./e2e/tests/...\\n\\n# Generate formatted report\\ngo run ./e2e/cmd/testreport -color -o \\\"$E2E_ARTIFACT_DIR/report.txt\\\" \\\\\\n  \\\"$E2E_ARTIFACT_DIR/test-events.json\\\"\\n```\\n\\n**Key flags:**\\n- `-tags=e2e` — Only runs tests with the `//go:build e2e` tag\\n- `-count=1` — Disables test caching (run once)\\n- `-timeout=30m` — Global timeout for all tests combined\\n- `--agent <name>` — Filters to single agent (or empty = all registered agents)\\n- `[filter]` — Regex filter passed to `-run` flag for test name matching\\n\\n### 2. **Test Results Output Locations**\\n\\nAll artifacts are saved to `E2E_ARTIFACT_DIR` (default: `e2e/artifacts/YYYY-MM-DDTHH-MM-SS/`):\\n\\n**For each test (subdirectory per test name):**\\n- `console.log` — Full transcript of agent stdout/stderr, git commands, checkpoint events\\n- `git-log.txt` — Commit history with graph visualization\\n- `git-tree.txt` — Working tree state + entire/checkpoints/v1 branch contents\\n- `entire-logs/` — Internal CLI logs from `.entire/logs/`\\n- `checkpoint-metadata/` — Checkpoint metadata extracted from git tree (sharded by checkpoint ID)\\n- `pane.txt` — Final tmux pane content (for interactive sessions)\\n- `PASS` or `FAIL` — Marker file indicating test outcome\\n\\n**Global test report files:**\\n- `test-events.json` — JSON event stream from `go test` (parsed by testreport)\\n- `report.txt` — Formatted human-readable test report with colors\\n- `report.nocolor.txt` — Plain text version of report (no ANSI codes)\\n- `entire-version.txt` — Binary path and