anic unexpected panics\\n        }\\n    }()\\n    fn(t, s, ctx)\\n    return false\\n}\\n```\\n\\n- If `RunPrompt()` detects a transient API error (rate limit, token refresh failure), it panics with `errScenarioRestart`\\n- `ForEachAgent` catches the panic and **restarts the entire scenario** with a fresh repository\\n- **Up to 3 total attempts** (`maxScenarioRestarts=2`, so 2 retries)\\n- Avoids stale CLI session state from failed attempts poisoning the retry\\n\\n### 5. **Artifact Capture**\\n\\n**Location:** `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_experiments/e2e/testutil/artifacts.go:49`\\n\\n`CaptureArtifacts()` is called automatically on test cleanup and captures:\\n\\n1. **Git state:** `git log --graph --all`, `git ls-tree` (working tree + metadata branch)\\n2. **Console log:** Already written incrementally via `RepoState.ConsoleLog` file handle\\n3. **Checkpoint metadata:** Extracted from `entire/checkpoints/v1` tree, sharded by checkpoint ID prefix\\n4. **Internal logs:** Copied from `.entire/logs/`\\n5. **Interactive session pane:** Final tmux pane content (if session was started)\\n6. **Pass/Fail marker:** `PASS` or `FAIL` file\\n\\n**Key design:** Console log is written incrementally to disk (survives global timeouts), and artifact capture is a cleanup function that runs LIFO after test completion.\\n\\n### 6. **Rerun/Retry Logic**\\n\\n**There is NO built-in test rerun mechanism in the E2E test system.** Instead:\\n\\n- **Transient errors** (API failures) trigger **scenario restart** (fresh repo) within the same test execution\\n- **Test failures** are NOT automatically retried (the test either passes or fails)\\n- **CI workflows** have `fail-fast: false` to run all agents even if one fails\\n- **Manual debugging:** Use `e2e-isolated.yml` workflow to run a single test with `-agent` and `[filter]` flags\\n\\n### 7. **GitHub Workflows**\\n\\n**`.github/workflows/e2e.yml`** (main E2E test run):\\n- Runs on push to `main` or manual dispatch\\n- Concurrency: On